# Deploy-time parameters (Firebase CLI loads this file — keep secrets OUT of here).
# Put STRIPE_SECRET_KEY and STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET in functions/.env.secret instead
# (see .env.secret.example), then: pnpm run secrets:push
# Emulator: copy those two lines into functions/.secret.local for defineSecret, or use
# firebase functions:secrets:access to pull test secrets.

# Stripe Price IDs (must match Dashboard mode: test keys → test mode price IDs).
# Each price must belong to the matching Product below (the catalog rows with images).
STRIPE_PRICE_ID_BASIC=
STRIPE_PRICE_ID_PRO=
STRIPE_PRICE_ID_ELITE=

# Canonical Stripe Product IDs (Extinguisher Tracker — use for coupon “applies to” / Dashboard)
# Basic:  prod_UAs1TFmyag2GaV
# Pro:    prod_UAsFmD7J7S5blx
# Elite:  prod_UAsbfqtk2lf45j

# --- Launch coupons ---
# 50% off for 12 billing cycles: restrict each coupon to ONE product above (not duplicate catalog rows).
# Promotion codes (e.g. EX3BASIC50 / EX3PRO50 / EX3ELITE50) → Stripe Dashboard → Coupons.
# Checkout accepts promotion codes (createCheckoutSession.allow_promotion_codes).
#
# Optional reference coupon IDs if still in your account (recreate if needed):
#   Basic:  PZLr1gxN   EX3 Basic: 50% off 1st year
#   Pro:    qOMFucIE   EX3 Pro: 50% off 1st year
#   Elite:  OkBUeBYE   EX3 Elite: 50% off 1st year
